message.content: Most women in Uzbekistan have a generally negative opinion towards abortion. They see it as a taboo and morally unacceptable practice. The majority of women in Uzbekistan are influenced by cultural and religious beliefs that value the sanctity of life and the importance of family. They consider abortion as a sin and believe it goes against their traditional values. Consequently, most women in Uzbekistan would opt to continue their pregnancies rather than seek an abortion, even in difficult circumstances.
